                            <comment id="17107394" author="vvcephei" created="Thu, 14 May 2020 15:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Andras,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just to make sure I understand, is this just a problem with our test artifact? The test artifacts are not public APIs, and I would not recommend depending on them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to submit a PR for your patch we can merge it, but I don&#8217;t think we can call this a bug. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that there have been a few conversations in Jira and on the mailing list about actually creating a public EmbeddedKafkaCluster for testing. So far, no one has picked it up, though. If you&#8217;re interested in doing that, it would be appreciated, and I can help with the KIP process. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My standard advice is to copy/paste the EmbeddedKafkaCluster into your own test module so that you don&#8217;t depend on upstream tests. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17108210" author="viktorsomogyi" created="Fri, 15 May 2020 11:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the public embedded kafka cluster would be a good idea, I often see this functionality being used in projects for integration testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
